What you need to know:

Nation Sport writer Samuel Gacharira spent a week visiting Kenya’s representatives at their respective bases and in this week-long series, he gives interesting insights on the behind-the-scenes work coaches and players have put in ahead of the continental eventIn less than four months, Melly had made his debut in the local league in KPA’s blue stripes, flirted with the idea of becoming a Kenya Prisons officer before finally settling down at their nemesis GSUMelly started playing volleyball at the age of 10 as a libero before shifting to setting in 2011 while still a Class Eight pupil at Simat Primary SchoolMelly laments the stagnation of the men’s game in Kenya which he believes has partly contributed to the poor performance of the national team and local clubs in continental assignments